K8s Nodes


This dashboard is populated by the metrics emitted from the kubernetes-cluster monitor and kubelet-stats . Charts below refer to the health of your Kubernetes Nodes. When filtered by Deployment or Service, charts below will be filtered by the selected pods running on the nodes.

chart.programText: A = data('pod_network_receive_bytes_total', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True), rollup='rate').sum().publish(label='A')

chart.description: Number of bytes that are consumed by the container on this filesystem
chart.name: Disk Usage
chart.programText: A = data('container_fs_usage_bytes', rollup='latest', extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=2).publish(label='A')

chart.description: per cluster
chart.name: Memory Usage
chart.programText: A = data('container_memory_usage_bytes').sum(by=['kubernetes_cluster']).publish(label='A')

chart.description: Based on Pod spec's resources.limits.cpu value if present, otherwise chart will be blank.
chart.name: % CPU Limit Used per Pod
chart.programText:
A = data('container_cpu_utilization', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True) and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True)).sum(by=['kubernetes_pod_name']).publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = data('container_spec_cpu_quota', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True) and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True)).sum(by=['kubernetes_pod_name']).publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = data('container_spec_cpu_period', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True) and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True)).sum(by=['kubernetes_pod_name']).publish(label='C', enable=False)
D = (A/(B/C)).sum(by=['kubernetes_pod_name']).publish(label='D')

chart.description: Total number of disk writes per second by containers in cluster(s)
chart.name: Disk Writes

publishLabelOptions.displayName: Cumulative count of seconds spent writing
publishLabelOptions.label: B

chart.programText:
A = data('container_fs_writes_total', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True), rollup='latest', extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=2).sum().publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = data('container_fs_write_seconds_total', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True), rollup='latest', extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=2).sum().publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = (A/B).publish(label='C')

chart.description: Based on Kubernetes resource limits.  If no limits, will be blank.
chart.name: % Memory Used per Pod
chart.programText:
A = data('container_memory_usage_bytes', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True) and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True)).sum(by=['kubernetes_pod_name']).publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = data('container_spec_memory_limit_bytes', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True) and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True)).sum(by=['kubernetes_pod_name']).above(0, inclusive=True).publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = (A/B*100).publish(label='C')

chart.description: per node
chart.name: Top 10 Nodes by Memory Capacity Used
chart.programText:
D = data('container_memory_usage_bytes', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*', match_missing=True)).sum(by=['kubernetes_cluster', 'host']).mean(over='1m').publish(label='D', enable=False)
E = data('machine_memory_bytes', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*', match_missing=True)).sum(by=['kubernetes_cluster', 'host']).mean(over='1m').publish(label='E', enable=False)
F = (D/E).scale(100).top(count=10).publish(label='F')

chart.name: # of Pods by Phase
chart.programText:
B = data('kubernetes.pod_phase', filter=filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True) and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True), rollup='latest').between(1.5, 2.5, low_inclusive=True, high_inclusive=True).count().publish(label='B')
A = data('kubernetes.pod_phase', filter=filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True) and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True), rollup='latest').between(0, 1.5, low_inclusive=True, high_inclusive=True).count().publish(label='A')
C = data('kubernetes.pod_phase', filter=filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True) and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True), rollup='latest').between(2.5, 3.5, low_inclusive=True, high_inclusive=True).count().publish(label='C')
D = data('kubernetes.pod_phase', filter=filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True) and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True), rollup='latest').between(3.5, 4.5, low_inclusive=True, high_inclusive=True).count().publish(label='D')
E = data('kubernetes.pod_phase', filter=filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True) and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True), rollup='latest').between(4.5, 5.5, low_inclusive=True, high_inclusive=True).count().publish(label='E')

chart.name: Network Throughput (bytes/sec)
chart.programText:
A = data('pod_network_receive_bytes_total', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True) and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True), extrapolation='zero').sum().publish(label='A')
B = data('pod_network_transmit_bytes_total', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True) and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True), extrapolation='zero').sum().publish(label='B')

chart.name: Available Pods by Deployment
chart.programText:
A = data('kubernetes.deployment.available').publish(label='A')
B = data('kubernetes.deployment.desired').publish(label='B', enable=False)

chart.name: Deployments Not at Spec
chart.programText:
A = data('kubernetes.deployment.available', extrapolation='zero').publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = data('kubernetes.deployment.desired', extrapolation='zero').publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = (B-A).above(0).count().publish(label='C')

options.markdown:
K8s Pods


Charts below refer to the health of your Kubernetes Pods. Use the filters at the top to narrow down pods by Cluster, Namespace, Nodes, Services, or Deployments.
Service tag syncing was added with agent version v4.1.0 and deployment property syncing in v4.3.0.

chart.description: Top 10 CPU usage by containers in cluster(s)
chart.name: CPU
chart.programText: A = data('container_cpu_utilization', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True), rollup='rate').top(count=10).publish(label='A')

chart.name: Pods by Phase
chart.programText:
A = data('kubernetes.pod_phase', rollup='latest').below(1, inclusive=True).count().publish(label='A')
B = data('kubernetes.pod_phase', rollup='latest').between(1.1, 2, low_inclusive=True, high_inclusive=True).count().publish(label='B')
C = data('kubernetes.pod_phase', rollup='latest').between(2.1, 3, low_inclusive=True, high_inclusive=True).count().publish(label='C')
D = data('kubernetes.pod_phase', rollup='latest').between(3.1, 4, low_inclusive=True, high_inclusive=True).count().publish(label='D')
E = data('kubernetes.pod_phase', rollup='latest').above(4).count().publish(label='E')

chart.description: grouped by cluster
chart.name: CPU Capacity Used per Node
chart.programText:
A = data('container_cpu_utilization', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True) and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True), rollup='rate').sum(by=['host', 'kubernetes_cluster', 'kubernetes_node']).publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = data('machine_cpu_cores', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_node', '*')).sum(by=['host']).publish(label='E', enable=False)
C = (A/B).publish(label='C')

chart.description: number of pods ready by deploments
chart.name: Available Pods by Deployments
chart.programText: A = data('kubernetes.deployment.available', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True), rollup='latest').sum(by=['kubernetes_cluster', 'kubernetes_namespace', 'kubernetes_name', 'kubernetes_uid']).sum().publish(label='A')

chart.description: Shows memory limit for the container if set
chart.name: Memory Limit
chart.programText: A = data('container_spec_memory_limit_bytes', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True) and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True) and filter('container_spec_name', '*') and filter('container_id', '*') and filter('kubernetes_pod_name', '*') and filter('kubernetes_pod_uid', '*'), rollup='latest', extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=2).publish(label='A')

chart.name: Network Errors / sec
chart.programText:
A = data('pod_network_receive_errors_total', filter=filter('metric_source', 'kubernetes')).sum().publish(label='A')
B = data('pod_network_transmit_errors_total', filter=filter('metric_source', 'kubernetes')).sum().publish(label='B')

chart.description: Top 10 cumulative count of memory allocation failures by type
chart.name: Memory Allocation Failures
chart.programText: A = data('container_memory_failures_total', filter=filter('scope', 'container'), rollup='latest', extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=2).top(count=10).publish(label='A')

chart.name: Desired Pods by Deployments
chart.programText: A = data('kubernetes.deployment.desired', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True), rollup='latest').sum(by=['kubernetes_cluster', 'kubernetes_namespace', 'kubernetes_name']).publish(label='A')

chart.description: created by Deployments
chart.name: Desired Pods
chart.programText: A = data('kubernetes.deployment.desired', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('deployment', '*', match_missing=True), rollup='latest').sum(by=['kubernetes_cluster', 'kubernetes_namespace']).sum().publish(label='A')

chart.name: Daemon Sets by Stage
chart.programText:
A = data('kubernetes.daemon_set.current_scheduled').sum(by=['kubernetes_cluster']).publish(label='A')
B = data('kubernetes.daemon_set.desired_scheduled').sum(by=['kubernetes_cluster']).publish(label='B')
C = data('kubernetes.daemon_set.misscheduled').sum(by=['kubernetes_cluster']).publish(label='C')
D = data('kubernetes.daemon_set.ready').sum(by=['kubernetes_cluster']).publish(label='D')

chart.name: Net Pods Desired by Replication Controller
chart.programText:
A = data('kubernetes.replication_controller.available').publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = data('kubernetes.replication_controller.desired').publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = (B-A).publish(label='C')
